free: #e "I will tell a story about a frog."
#c 我要說關於一隻青蛙的故事。
#e "This story about a child and a dog."
#c 這個故事是關於一隻狗和一個小孩。
#e "(They) kept it in a jar to raise."
#e "The child was still asleep on his bed."
#e "The child and the dog went to look for the frog."
#c 小孩和狗跑去找那隻青蛙。
#e "They looked for the frog which was in the jar."
#c 他們找原來在甕裡的青蛙。
#e "The boy came to look for the frog."
#c 小孩在他的東西之間四處翻找。
#e "The child turned his shoes upside down, but he couldn't find (the frog)."
#c 小孩把他的鞋倒過來，但是找不到青蛙。
#e "The dog looked inside the jar. The frog was not there too."
#c 狗找甕的裡面，青蛙不在那裡。
#e "Would the frog know the sound (calling it)?"
#c 青蛙認不認得那個聲音（在叫牠）？
#e "The dog forced itself toward the jar."
#e "The dog inserted its head into the jar."
#e "The dog got itself into the jar to look for the frog there."
#c 狗讓自己進到甕裡面找青蛙。
#e "Let's go and look for the frog."
#e "They went out to the grasses to look for the frog."
#c 他們出去到草原上找青蛙。
#e "The boy went out of the house and called."
#c 孩子跑出去房子外面叫。
#e "They went into the woods and kept on calling."
#e "They called and called but did not see the frog come out."
#c 他們叫啊叫，但是沒有看到青蛙出來。
#e "The boy came to the mouse hole."
#e "The dog was pushing and shaking the tree."
#e "The bees falling on the ground flew away."
#c 那些掉在地上的蜂飛走了。
#e "The child looked for the frog up the tree."
#c 有東西進去（樹上）腐壞的樹洞。
#e "He went to peek inside the hole."
#e "The dog ran away from the bees chasing it."
#e "They ran away passing under the tree."
#c 他們跑著離開經過那棵樹。
#c 當他們已經跑得很遠了，
#e "It seemed like it's attacking the child."
#c 好像是牠在攻擊那個小孩。
#e "The child climbed on top of the rock calling the frog."
#c 小孩爬到石頭上面叫青蛙。
#e "The dog lay down beside the rock."
#e "Who passed by there to look for the frog?"
#e "And came on top of the rock."
#e "The deer ran away toward a spacious area there."
#c 鹿朝著一個寬闊的地方跑去。

gloss: 第一人稱複數排除予格

free: #e "The dog also chased along and came to a cliff."
#e "The deer stopped (and prevented the dog from bumping into it)."
#c 鹿停下來 （並且避免狗跳上去）。
#e "The child also fell into a shady spot."
#n (an)指音檔中聽不見但發音人覺得應該有的部份
#n Note: -an- is inaudible in the sound file, but Informant feels it should be there.
#e "The child fell into a shady area together with his dog."
#c 小孩和他的狗一起掉下去到蔭涼處。
#e "The deer looked carefully from the top."
#e "The child and the dog knew how to swim."
#e "The dog sat down and climbed on top of the child's shoulder."
#c 那狗坐下，並爬上小孩的肩膀。
#e "The deer was still on top of the mountain."
#e "It came down and regretted it. And said,"
#c 牠下來並且很後悔,並且說，
#e "They came to the side of a shady spot."
#c 他們來到蔭涼的這一邊。
#e "The child told the dog to be quiet."
#e "They climbed on top of a dead wood."
#c 他們（爬）上那木頭的頂端。
#e "The child looked down to look for the frog."
#e "He saw two frogs behind the dead piece of wood."
#c 他看到兩隻青蛙在那塊木頭後面。
#e "What's wrong with the dog and the child?"
#e "They were sitting on top of the dead piece of wood."
#c 牠們坐在那塊木頭上面。
#e "Now the child caught... , found his frog."
#c 現在小孩捉 ... .找到他的青蛙。
#e "So there will be fewer frogs swimming in the shady area."
#c 因此會有一些青蛙在那蔭涼處游泳。
#e "The child bade farewell to the group of frogs."
